<p><b>Democratic socialism</b> is a description used by various <a href="/wiki/Socialism" title="Socialism">socialist</a> movements, tendencies, and organizations, to emphasize the democratic character of their political orientation. The term is sometimes used synonymously with '<a href="/wiki/Social_democracy" title="Social democracy">social democracy</a>', but many self-identified<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since March 2009" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup> democratic socialists oppose social democracy, seeing it as capitalist.</p>
